About Vered

More than movement —
a practice.

I'm Vered, and I've been guiding students through the transformative power of Pilates for over a decade here in Dallas. My approach blends classical technique with a deep understanding of functional anatomy — so every session is both safe and genuinely effective.

Whether you're recovering from injury, building athletic performance, or simply seeking a stronger, more balanced body — I meet you exactly where you are.

Why Vered

What sets this studio
apart.

01

Personalized Approach

No two bodies are the same. Every session is tailored to your anatomy, goals, and current fitness level — no cookie-cutter classes here.

02

Clinical Expertise

With a background in movement rehabilitation, Vered works safely with postpartum clients, injury recovery, and chronic pain management.

03

Boutique Experience

Small group sizes mean you always get personal attention and real corrections — not just a number in a crowded room.

04

Full Equipment Access

Reformer, Tower, Wunda Chair, Ladder Barrel — a complete classical studio designed for your full progression.

05

Flexible Scheduling

Morning, evening, and weekend sessions available. Private appointments built around your Dallas lifestyle.

06

Real Results

Clients report better posture, reduced back pain, and increased core strength within 8–12 weeks of consistent practice.
